RIGHTS REPRESENTED HEREBY WILL EXPIRE JUNE 15, 1932
No. S 505
of a Share
SCRIP CERTIFICATE
21sts
For Capital Stock of
Aviation Corporation of the Americas
(Incorporated under the laws of the State of Delaware).
Issued by
The Chase National Bank of the City of New York
THIS CERTIFIES that
-JAMES H. RAND-
has an Interest to the extent of
-TWELVE (wenty-frets of a share in the shares of full paid and non-assessable apital stock, without
par value, of AVIATION CORPORATION OF THE AMERICAS (a Delaware corporation), hereinafter referred to as the Company, held by the undersigned for the account of the regis-
tered holders of this and other similar scrip certificates and is entitled to the following, but no other, rights in respect of such interest:
At any time prior to the sale, as hereinafter set forth, of the shares of capital stock of the Company held by the undersigned in respect of this and other similar scrip cer-

the undersigned, duly endorsed and stamped, calling in the aggregate for one or more full shares of such capital stock, the holder hereof will be entitled to receive, in exchange therefor
(a) a stock certificate or certificates for the aggregate number of full shares of capital stock of the Company, as constituted at the date hereof, called for by the scrip certificates so
surrendered, and (b) a new sorip certificate issued by the undersigned, bearing the same date as this serip certificate for any fraction of a share of such capital stock called for by the
scrip certificates so surrendered.
Any dividends received by the undersigned upon the shares of capital stock of the Company represented by the stock certificate or certiticates so
delivered which shall have been declared payable to the holder of such shares of record as of the date prior to the surrender of such scrip certificates will be paid to or on the order of
the holder of such scrip certifloates upon surrender thereof as aforesaid.
At any time after the sale by the undersigned, as hereinafter set forth, of the shares of stock held by it in respect of this and other like scrip certificates issued by the under-
signed, the holder of this certificate upon surrender hereof as aforesaid shall be entitled to receive the proportion applicable to the fraction of a share of capital stock of the Company
with respect to which this scrip certificate was issued, of (a) the net cash proceeds from the sale of such shares, and (b) any dividends received by the undersigned in respect of such
shares which shall have been declared payable to the holders of such shares of reoord as of a date prior to the sale thereof by the undersigned.
At any time after June 15, 1932, the undersigned may sell, at public or private sale, without notice to the holder hereof, for the account of the holders of this and other similar
sorip certificates, the shares of capital stock of the Company held by the undersigned hereunder and thereunder.
In case any subscription rights shall be received by the undersigned with respect to the shares of capital stock of the Company from time to time held by the undersigned in
respect of tals sorip certificate and other like scrip certificates issued by the undersigned, the undersigned will endeavor to sell such subscription rights, as soon as possible after the receipt
